In the present work, we select 25 complete virus genomes: 12 coronaviruses from the three isolated typical groups, 12 SARS-CoV strains, and a torovirus, which serves as the outgroup for coronaviruses [28] (Table 1
). Pairwise distance matrices for these 25 sequences are calculated using our distances (D1, D2 and D3) and the classical relative entropy. Notice that RE does not satisfy the symmetry condition. We use the sum of RE(A,B) and RE(B,A) instead. Then, phylogenetic trees are built from these matrices using the UPGMA program in the PHYLIP package [29]. Finally, rooted phylogenetic trees are drawn by TREEVIEW program [30], and some of them are shown in Fig. 1, Fig. 2
.
